news.title: Sanskar Projects & Housing dragged to NCLT over default
news.para: Real Pro Realty Solutions, has preferred section 7 application before the NCLT Delhi against Sanskar Projects, for the default committed, towards the payment of a financial debt, due to RealPro.

news.title: Smartworks takes seven lakh sq ft office space on lease in Bengaluru
news.para: The Noida-based company, which has taken the office space from Bengaluru-based real estate developer Vaishnavi Tech Park, said that it is the single largest flexible office space transaction in India.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body's town planning department makes Rs 15 crore in just four months
news.para: Of the 830 building proposals, the town planning (TP) department cleared 469 by July 31. Most of these proposals were for individual houses and some were for housing projects by builders.

news.title: Authority asks consultant to prepare New Noida master plan by Aug 31
news.para: Officials said that on Sunday that the Authority representatives, in a meeting last week, had raised several queries about land pooling and the plan to connect the area with the Noida International Airport, apart from several other upcoming projects in Greater Noida.

news.title: Registry of Rajasthan housing board flats in high-rise buildings cheaper
news.para: The stamp duty levied on the registry of flats constructed in multi-storeyed buildings, having a value of less than Rs 50 lakh, has been reduced from 6% to 4%.

news.title: Indore civic body issues notices to 30,000 newly identified properties
news.para: These properties were found during an ongoing GIS survey, and their respective owners have been issued notices for registration and property tax payment, said officials.

news.title: Over 4.10 lakh houses under PMAY-Gramin yet to be built in Rajasthan
news.para: Minister of state in the ministry of rural development Sadhvi Niranjan Jyoti informed this on July 19 while replying to an unstarred question in Lok Sabha.

news.title: PNB Housing may re-enter corporate loans at appropriate time: Hardayal Prasad, CEO
news.para: The loan book declined by 45 per cent in the first quarter of 2022-23 compared to the year-ago period on account of sell-offs and accelerated prepayments.

news.title: Illegal farmhouses crop up as DDA's Green Development Area policy is delayed
news.para: According to industry bodies, several representations have been made to the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) and ministry of housing & urban affairs (MoHUA), triggered by the demand for farmhouses during the Covid-19 pandemic.

news.title: Maharashtra: ULPIN data integration in process to check land frauds
news.para: Commonly called Aadhaar for land, the 11-digit ULPIN would be attributed to all the land parcels in urban and rural areas in the state. It would help identify every surveyed land parcel and prevent any land frauds.

news.title: Maharashtra unlikely to implement Model Tenancy Act, says state law strong
news.para: Confirming the communication by the state to the Centre, the state housing department official said Maharashtra has no intention to implement the act, as the existing state rental act was strong enough.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA tells AOAs & builders to not charge owners extra for flat sale
news.para: Residents had complained to the authority that while selling flats, AOAs or builders seek lakhs of rupees before issuing a no-objection certificate to them. Officials said that it is illegal and comes in the category of corruption.

news.title: NGT directs authorities to connect 93 villages of Greater Noida with sewage network
news.para: The green panel noted the villages have been provided with internal drains but these are yet to be connected to the main sewer line.

news.title: Supertech to give structural audit info of twin towers as sought by CBRI by Aug 7
news.para: CBRI's approval is required for Edifice to go ahead with the charging -- rigging of the twin towers with explosives -- at the site, a process which would need them around 15 days.

news.title: Lucknow development body to release Rs 18 crore to spruce up its 15 RWAs
news.para: The Resident Welfare Associations (RWA) of the respective buildings will use the fund for maintenance and repairing of buildings, including the lifts and generators.
